What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Glass Fiber-reinforced Plastics (GFRP) Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Glass fiber-reinforced plastics (GFRP) are produced by fiberglass and are used widely in commercial and industrial applications due to their lightweight and durability. They usually have high tensile strength and flexibility as compared to metals. These materials are widely used in industries like aerospace, construction, automotive, marine, electrical, and others. They are also used to create various types of composite materials.

Data Bridge Market Research analyzes that the global glass fiber-reinforced plastics (GFRP) market, which was USD 44.68 billion in 2022, would rocket up to USD 95.67 billion by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 6.55% during the forecast period.

Increasing demand for GFRP in the transportation industry is a vital factor escalating the market growth, also a rise in the number of wind energy capacity installations, an increase in the usage of GFRP composite pipes in sewage & water management, a rise in the use of GFRP composites in the construction & infrastructure industry are the major factors driving the growth of Glass Fiber-reinforced Plastics (GFRP) market. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

